-- British Supermarkets Buying Less South African Wine, Business Day Reports
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 2010-12-22T05:22:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/british-supermarkets-buying-less-south-african-wine-business-day-reports.html
Sales of South African-packaged
wines to British supermarkets fell 29 percent during the last 11
months amid a global recession and competition from other wine
makers, Business Day reported, citing Jo Wehring, the U.K.
market manager for Wines of SA, an industry body.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  